    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Beware of Artificial Life</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Rossi letter on Aug 31 article says manufactured worries about self-replicating robots easily supplants more substantial worries</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Scientists Report They Have Made Robot That Makes Its Own Robots'' (front page, Aug. 31):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Scientists Report They Have Made Robot That Makes Its Own Robots'' (front page, Aug. 31):</p>
        <p>As the scientist Bill Joy commented, we shouldn't create a race of killer robots to supplant mankind. But the same prudence might be exercised with respect to the genetically engineered plants and animals currently being released willy-nilly into the environment.</p>
        <p>The possible negative effects of these kinds of self-replicating, evolving machines are complex and difficult to predict.</p>
        <p>The fact that manufactured concerns about emerging technologies should so easily supplant substantive concerns is truly a development to be worried about.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL ROSSI  New York, Aug. 31, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
